Anthrax, Kyrgyzstan
---------------------
Information received on [and dated] 30 Aug 2013 from Dr Djanybek Sultanov, Deputy Director, Chief State Veterinary Inspector, State Inspectorate on Veterinary and Phytosanitary Security, Ministry of Agriculture and Food, Bishkek, Kyrgyzstan

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 24 Aug 2013
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 24 Aug 2013
Report date: 30 Aug 2013
Date submitted to OIE: 30 Aug 2013
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 29 Sep 2008
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, Laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1: Lebedinovka, Alamudun, Chuy
Date of start of the outbreak: 24 Aug 2013
Outbreak status: Resolved (24 Aug 2013)
Epidemiological unit: Village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 9 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost (Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter)
Cattle / 11.11 percent / 11.11 percent / 100.00 percent / 11.11 percent

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: Quarantine, Movement control inside the country, Vaccination in response to the outbreak(s) (Total vaccinated: 153, cattle, Chuy), Disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s), No treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
National Veterinary Diagnosis Centre (National laboratory) / Cattle / bacteriological examination / 24 Aug 2013 / Positive

Future reporting:
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

Map of outbreak locations [Go to the source URL to see this map. The outbreak is in central Kyrgyzstan close to the Kazakh border. - Mod.MHJ]

